-- Three al-Qaeda Militants Killed in Yemen, Bomb Workshop Found
-- B y   M o h a m m e d   H a t e m
-- 2012-10-02T07:16:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-02/three-al-qaeda-militants-killed-in-yemen-bomb-workshop-found.html
Three al-Qaeda militants including a
Somali national were killed today when Yemeni security forces
stormed a houses in the port city of Aden, al-Jumhoriah state
newspaper said in a text message.  The Defense Ministry website said in a text message that
the security forces discovered a workshop the militants were
using to make explosives including car bombs. They seized a
large number of explosives as well as explosive belts and car
bombs, according to the message.  The ministry website said in another text message that
security forces found a plan indicating the militants intended
to target military and security leaders. Four police officers
were wounded in the operation, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
